[{"id":"92514cfdee192fa17f982f7b0e59203f","from":"Lesley Groff","from_email":"lesley@nysgllc.com","to":"J. Epstein","to_list":[{"name":"J. Epstein","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"FW: For Mr. Jeffrey Epstein-MICHAEL CLAYTON/30th","date":"2007-09-27T12:35:18.000Z","formatted_date":"Sep 27, 2007","formatted_time":"12:35 PM","body":" \n\n \n\nFrom: Peggy Siegal [mailto:peggy@peggysiegal.com] \nSent: Wednesday, September 26, 2007 4:16 PM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nSubject: For Mr. Jeffrey Epstein-MICHAEL CLAYTON/30th\n\n \n\n \n<http://rs6.net/on.jsp?t=1101825044681.0.1101430287919.1189&ts=S0278&o=h\nttp://ui.constantcontact.com/images/p1x1.gif> \n\n \n\nPlease come join George Clooney, Tilda Swinton and Tony Gilroy at their\nintimate private screening of \"Michael Clayton.\" No red carpet, no\npaparazzi, no press. It's just a terrific low key Sunday night with the\nfilmmakers and their friends.\n\n \n\nxxoo\n\n \n\nPeggy\n\n \n\nWarner Bros. Pictures \n\nSamuels Media and Castle Rock Entertainment\n\ninvite you to join\n\nGeorge Clooney   Tilda Swinton\n\nand writer and director Tony Gilroy\n\nat a private screening of\n\nMICHAEL CLAYTON\n\nSunday, September 30, 2007\n\n7:00pm The Time Warner Theater\n\nOne Time Warner Center, 10th floor\n\nenter at 58th Street between 8th & 9th Avenues\n\n9:00pm dinner hosted by Edmiston & Company\n\nNicholas Edmiston, Chairman\n\n&\n\nDiego Marroquin, Vice President\n\nPorter House New York\n\n10 Columbus Circle, 4th floor\n\npeggy@peggysiegal.com or 212-935-6700\n\nthis invitation is non-transferable\n\nconfirmed guests\n\nBob Balaban\n\nTory Burch\n\nLauren Bush\n\nGeorge Clooney\n\nKenneth Cole\n\nWalter Cronkite\nTony Gilroy\n\nLara Spencer\n\nRobert Wood Johnson\n\nBill Keller\n\nJames Kelly\n\nJared Kushner\n\nMatt Lauer\n\nJulianna Margulies\n\nBennett Miller\n\nSam Newhouse\n\nPete Peterson\n\nRegis Philbin\n\nNick Pileggi & Nora Ephron\n\nSteve Samuels\n\nHoward Schultz\n\nTilda Swinton\n\nIvanka Trump\n\nBarbara Walters\n\nVicky Ward\n\nStrauss Zelnick\n\nMichael Clayton (GEORGE CLOONEY) is an in-house \"fixer\" at one of the\nlargest corporate law firms in New York.  A former criminal prosecutor,\nClayton takes care of Kenner, Bach & Ledeen's dirtiest work at the\nbehest of the firm's co-founder Marty Bach (SYDNEY POLLACK).  Though\nburned out and hardly content with his job, his divorce, a failed\nbusiness venture and mounting debt have left Clayton inextricably tied\nto the firm.  \n\n \n\n             At U/North, meanwhile, the career of litigator Karen\nCrowder (TILDA SWINTON) rests on the multi-million dollar settlement of\na class action suit that Clayton's firm is leading to a seemingly\nsuccessful conclusion.  But when Kenner Bach's brilliant and\nguilt-ridden attorney Arthur Edens (TOM WILKINSON) sabotages the U/North\ncase, Clayton faces the biggest challenge of his career and his life.\n\n \n\n \n\n \n<http://visitor.constantcontact.com/d.jsp?p=un&m=1101430287919&se=1189&t\n=1101825044681&lang=en&reason=F> \n\nThis email was sent to lesley@nysgllc.com, by peggy@peggysiegal.com\n\nUpdate Profile/Email Address\n<http://visitor.constantcontact.com/d.jsp?p=oo&m=1101430287919&se=1189&t\n=1101825044681&lang=en&reason=F>  | Instant removal with SafeUnsubscribe\n<http://visitor.constantcontact.com/d.jsp?p=un&m=1101430287919&se=1189&t\n=1101825044681&lang=en&reason=F> (tm) | Privacy Policy\n<http://ui.constantcontact.com/roving/CCPrivacyPolicy.jsp> .\n\n\t\n\nPeggy Siegal | 4 West 58th Street | mezzanine | New York | NY | 10019 \n\n \n\n","body_html":"<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" xmlns:m=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40\">\n\n<head>\n<META HTTP-EQUIV=\"Content-Type\" CONTENT=\"text/html; charset=us-ascii\">\n<meta name=Generator content=\"Microsoft Word 12 (filtered medium)\">\n<!--[if !